- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Mobile Ad Hoc Networks and MAC-layer protocols. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with distributed networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses communication interference. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper presents a calculus for modeling and studying protocols. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents a Reduction Semantics and a Labelled Transition Semantics.
